			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">How closely related do you want the emu to emulate the actual EQ servers?  I ask this because it could help you determine some factors for your questions.  For example, NPCs or mobs attacking a weaker PC is pretty much standard practice for mobs unless the tank is using taunt.  I.e. Most casters will be attacked by mobs in a group situation unless the casters have backed off - but even then, if the spell cast upon a mob does a large amount of damage in one strike, the mob will attempt to go after that caster unless, again, distracted by the tank(s).
<br />

<br />
When soloing with a pet (i.e. necro), the mob will not concentrate on the pet unless the PC has backed off.  They will attack the PC *always* if that person is within attacking range regardless of the pet.  However, if the PC is at less than about 30% health, it is near impossible to taunt the mob off until either the mob is killed or the PC is.
<br />

<br />
Now for the other poll question: NPC's should react to other NPC's the same as they would react to PC's in regard to hate/faction.  (Ever seen a decaying skellie attack a black wolf?  It happens all the time and is rather interesting to watch).  What do you suppose would happen if the guards in North Freeport mysteriously ended up in the same zones as the Freeport Militia?  Now *That* would be an interesting rumble to watch.  As for PvP, I've never seen any more than five faction hits per given mob or quest whether positive or negative so I would say select the top 10 negative and positive factions (provided that they are high-end factions - i.e. ally, or attack) and then choose the top five from that list.
<br />

<br />
As for a group situation and faction, I think it would be best if all members of the party took equal faction hits...after all, they were all in on the battle together - guilty by association, so to speak.
<br />

<br />
I think that covers everything... <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />- Khevor</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
