			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hmm.  I think the group should take equal faction hits.
<br />

<br />
I am not a big PvP fan but I would think you should only take faction hits with that players base faction.  Ie. if you killed a woodelf ranger you would take a hit with Faydwer Champions, guards, merchants, etc.  But you wouldn't take hits with other things that he is ally to.  You would gain faction with opposing races like Dark Elves, etc.
<br />

<br />
As to agro, I think each mob should have their own agro table.  Part of the challenge in a multi-mob encounter is to keep the agro off of the other players.  Take AOE groups for example.  If all mobs were on the same hate table then a tank could taunt one mob and the wizzards chould AoE with no reprocusion or risk.  This would eliviate the need for an enchanter.  It also makes the game too easy.
<br />

<br />
oh, one other thing on faction.  I think only guard type mobs should assist you if you have good faction.  If I am ally with a vendor and attack a mob they should not assist.  If I am warmly to wolfs and I attack something the wolf is not KoS to then it should not join the fight.  To make it otherwise would lessen the challenge of a lot of zones.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Another question is pet factions.  Should a pet have the same factions as the master or only if the master has it attack something?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
