				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First, I could care less if this emu closely matches EQLive. I would prefer the flexibility to make changes as one see fit for his/her server. I for one would make several changes to spawn rates.
<br />

<br />
As for factions (if possible), here is a thought. For some factions, the closer you are to a race/monster's home, the greater the faction hit. It has been a while since I played, so my data is only hypothetical... example: Consider Wood Elf city (felwithe?) - Killing a wood elf npc in Greater Faydark should give a bigger faction hit than killing a wood elf npc on an island in Ocean of Tears that is not even on the boat path. Or killing orcs in Antonica should not give a big faction hit for killing orcs in Faydark, or maybe no faction hit in Faydark.
<br />

<br />
I would also say that the simpler the race/monster, the shorter distance factions should travel.
<br />

<br />
It most likely would not be easy to do, and may not be possible either, just a thought. I always thought many of the factions in EQ were unrealistic, even for a game.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
